1 AN ACT concerning motor vehicle liability insurance; providing for the
2 establishment of a web-based online insurance verification system for
3 the verification of evidence of motor vehicle liability insurance;
4 amending K.S.A. 8-173 and repealing the existing section.
5
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of the State of Kansas:
7 New Section 1. (a) Sections 1 through 9{10}, and amendments
8 thereto, shall be known and may be cited as the Kansas real time motor
9 vehicle insurance verification act.
10 (b) As used in this act:
11 (1) "Act" means the Kansas real time motor vehicle insurance
12 verification act.
13 (2) "Commercial vehicle coverage" means any coverage provided to
14 an insured, regardless of number of vehicles covered, under a commercial
15 coverage form and rated from a commercial manual approved by the
16 department.
17 (3) "Commissioner" means the commissioner of insurance.
18 (4) "Department" means the Kansas insurance department.
19 (5) "Insurance verification system" means the web-based system for
20 online verification of motor vehicle liability insurance.
21 (6) "KDOR" means the Kansas department of revenue.
22 New Sec. 2. (a) The commissioner shall establish a web-based system
23 for online verification of motor vehicle insurance and require motor
24 vehicle insurers to establish functionality for such system, as specified in
25 this act. Implementation of the insurance verification system, including
26 any exceptions as provided for in this act, supersedes any existing motor
27 vehicle liability insurance verification system requirements and shall be
28 the sole electronic system used for the purpose of verifying motor vehicle
29 liability insurance as required by the laws of Kansas.
30 (b) The commissioner shall adopt such reasonable rules and
31 regulations as are necessary to effectuate the provisions of this act.
32 New Sec. 3. (a) The insurance verification system shall:
33 (1) (A) Transmit requests to insurers for verification of motor vehicle
34 liability insurance via web services established by the insurers in

SB 42—Am. by SCW 2
1 compliance with specifications and standards prescribed by the
2 commissioner in rules and regulations; and
3 (B) insurance company systems shall respond to each request for
4 verification of motor vehicle liability insurance with a prescribed response
5 upon evaluation of the data provided in such request;
6 (2) include appropriate provisions to secure its data against
7 unauthorized access in accordance with applicable data privacy protection
8 laws;
9 (3) be used for verification of motor vehicle liability insurance as
10 prescribed by the laws of Kansas and shall be accessible to authorized
11 personnel of the department, KDOR division of vehicles, the courts, law
12 enforcement agencies and other entities authorized by state or federal
13 privacy laws;
14 (4) be interfaced, wherever appropriate, with existing state systems;
15 and
16 (5) include information that shall enable authorized personnel to
17 make inquiries of insurers of motor vehicle liability insurance by using
18 multiple data elements for greater matching accuracy, including, but not{.
19 Such information shall be} limited to:
20 (A) Insurer national association of insurance commissioners company
21 code number;
22 (B) vehicle identification number;
23 (C) policy number;
24 (D) verification date; or
25 (E) any other information required by the commissioner or KDOR to
26 operate the insurance verification system.
27 New Sec. 4. The commissioner may conduct a competitive bid and
28 contract with a private service provider that has successfully implemented
29 similar systems in other states to assist in establishing, implementing and
30 maintaining the insurance verification system.
31 New Sec. 5. The department shall provide funding for the
32 implementation, ongoing maintenance and enhancement of the insurance
33 verification system created by this act from the insurance department
34 regulation service fund, established under K.S.A. 40-112, and amendments
35 thereto.
36 New Sec. 6. (a) Insurers shall cooperate with the commissioner and
37 KDOR in establishing and maintaining the insurance verification system
38 and provide motor vehicle insurance policy status information as provided
39 in rules and regulations established by the commissioner.
40 (b) Insurer systems shall be permitted reasonable system downtime
41 for maintenance and other work with advance notice to KDOR. Insurers
42 shall not be subject to enforcement fees or other penalties under such
43 circumstances or when systems are unavailable because of emergency,

SB 42—Am. by SCW 3
1 outside attack or other unexpected outages not planned by the insurer and
2 that are reasonably outside its control as determined by KDOR.
3 (c) Each property and casualty insurance company that is licensed to
4 issue motor vehicle liability insurance or is authorized to do business in
5 Kansas shall provide verification of liability insurance for every motor
6 vehicle insured in Kansas by such company as required by this act.
7 (d) This act shall not apply to vehicles insured under commercial
8 motor vehicle coverage, except that insurers of such vehicles may
9 participate on a voluntary basis.
10 (e) Insurers shall not be required to verify evidence of insurance for
11 vehicles registered in other jurisdictions.
12 (f) Insurers shall be immune from civil and administrative liability for
13 good faith efforts to comply with the terms of this act.
14 (g) Nothing in this section shall prohibit an insurer from using the
15 services of a third-party vendor to facilitate the insurance verification
16 program required by this act.
17 New Sec. 7. The commissioner may establish, through rules and
18 regulations, an alternative method for verifying motor vehicle liability
19 insurance for insurers that insure 1,000 or fewer vehicles within Kansas.
20 New Sec. 8. All information and data provided by insurance
21 companies to the insurance verification system, and all reports, responses
22 or other information generated for the purposes of the insurance
23 verification system shall be confidential by law and privileged, shall not be
24 subject to the open records act, K.S.A. 45-215, and amendments thereto,
25 and shall not be subject to discovery or admissible as evidence in any
26 private civil action.
27 New Sec. 9. The insurance verification system shall be fully
28 operational not later than July 1, 2026, following an appropriate testing
29 period of not less than nine months. No enforcement action shall be taken
30 based on information obtained from the insurance verification system until
31 such system has successfully completed the testing period.
32 {New Sec. 10. Establishing compliance with the provisions of
33 K.S.A. 40-3104, and amendments thereto, through the insurance
34 verification system shall not be the primary cause for law enforcement to
35 stop a vehicle.}
